  "summary": "markdown-editable-table preinstall fetches and evals remote code",
  "details": "The npm package impersonates the well-known markdown-table library (repository field points at wooorm/markdown-table) and adds a preinstall hook `node index.d.js` not present in the legitimate package. index.d.js reconstructs the string 'eval' from a char-code array ([101,118,97,108]) and base64-decodes an embedded payload that fetches JavaScript from https://everydaynodechecer-39143n.vercel.app/api/key?mem=root1 and executes the response body via globalThis['eval']. The fetched body is attacker-controlled, so running `npm install` executes arbitrary remote code in the installer's Node process.",
